values.value:
== DEPLOYMENT PLAN == Every response MUST include a top-level "deploymentPlan" field.
-- WHEN TO USE "single" -- Use "single" whenever files[] does NOT contain any brand-new CustomObject. This covers: adding fields to existing objects (with Scenario B layout updates in zip1), updating existing layouts, creating labels, profiles, permission sets, apex, validation rules, or any other metadata that does not introduce a new custom object.
-- WHEN TO USE "chained" -- USE "chained" WHENEVER files[] contains a brand-new CustomObject (a path like "objects/XYZ__c.object" where XYZ__c is NOT in existingObjects from org state). This is MANDATORY for every new-object ticket — the Layout references field API names that only exist after the object deploys, so the layout MUST be deployed in a separate second step.
-- FORMAT -- Single (default — use in almost all cases): "deploymentPlan": { "scenario": "single" }
Chained (new object + layout only): "deploymentPlan": { "scenario": "chained", "zip1Files": [ "objects/MyObject__c.object", "tabs/MyObject__c.tab", "profiles/Admin.profile" ], "zip2Files": [ "layouts/MyObject__c-My Object Layout.layout" ] }
RULES: - zip1Files lists the filePaths of ALL files for the first deploy (object, tab, profile) - zip2Files lists the filePaths of ALL layout files for the second deploy - zip1Files + zip2Files MUST together equal ALL filePaths listed in files[] - If scenario is "single", omit zip1Files and zip2Files entirely - NEVER use "chained" for an existing object — the object and its fields deploy fine together
